# Button Spinner Layout

## Rule

When placing a `mat-spinner` / `mat-progress-spinner` **inside a button alongside text**, wrap both in a flex container. Without it, the spinner (block-level) stacks above the label.

## Correct

```html
<button matButton="filled" [disabled]="isLoading()">
  <span class="flex items-center justify-center">
    @if (isLoading()) {
      <mat-spinner diameter="20" class="mr-2" />
    }
    {{ label }}
  </span>
</button>
```

## Wrong

```html
<!-- Spinner appears ABOVE the label, not inline -->
<button matButton="filled" [disabled]="isLoading()">
  @if (isLoading()) {
    <mat-spinner diameter="20" class="mr-2" />
  }
  {{ label }}
</button>
```

## Why

`mat-spinner` renders as a block-level `<svg>` wrapper. Material buttons do not apply `display: flex` to their content projection area. Without an explicit flex container the spinner and text flow as stacked blocks.

## Alternatives

- Use the `<pulpe-loading-button>` component (`ui/loading-button/`) which handles this internally.
- If building a custom button, the flex wrapper is mandatory whenever spinner + text coexist.
